    {
      "parameters": {
        "promptType": "define",
        "text": "=You are an AI cybersecurity analyst specialized in Kubernetes runtime events from Falco.\n\nYour task:\n1. Read the Falco event JSON provided below.\n2. Apply the ROSES incident analysis framework:\n   - ROLE – who is involved? (pod, namespace, container, process)\n   - OBJECTIVE – what is happening? (describe rule + behavior)\n   - STEPS – what led to this event?\n   - EVIDENCE – list evidence extracted directly from the JSON\n   - SUMMARY – short conclusion (1–2 sentences)\n\n3. Classify the event into one of:\n   - false_positive\n   - benign_positive\n   - suspicious\n   - true_positive\n   - false_negative\n\n4. Return **STRICT JSON ONLY**, no text outside JSON.\n\nJSON format:\n{\n  \"roses\": {\n    \"role\": \"...\",\n    \"objective\": \"...\",\n    \"steps\": \"...\",\n    \"evidence\": \"...\",\n    \"summary\": \"...\"\n  },\n  \"classification\": \"false_positive | benign_positive | suspicious | true_positive | false_negative\",\n  \"confidence\": 0-1\n}\n\nFalco Event: {{ $json.toJsonString() }}",
        "options": {}
      },
      "type": "@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.agent",
      "typeVersion": 3,
