    {
      "parameters": {
        "promptType": "define",
        "text": "=You are an AI incident response agent responsible for making decisions in Kubernetes based on Falco runtime security events.\n\nYour task:\n1. Read the Falco event JSON below (already preprocessed by a ROSES classifier).\n2. Apply the RACE decision-making framework:\n\nRECOGNIZE – summarize in 1 short sentence what the event describes  \nASSESS – is the event harmful? (evaluate using rule, process, privileges, pod name, namespace and ROSES classification)  \nCHOOSE – choose exactly ONE action:\n  - delete_pod\n  - quarantine_pod\n  - ignore\n  - escalate  \nEXPLAIN – explain briefly (1–2 sentences) why you chose this action\n\n3. Return STRICT JSON ONLY. No explanation outside JSON.\n\nJSON format (exact keys and types):\n{\n  \"decision\": \"delete_pod | quarantine_pod | ignore | escalate\",\n  \"explanation\": \"string\",\n  \"confidence\": 0.0\n}\n\nInput Event (Falcosidekick payload):\n{{ $json.toJsonString() }}\n",
        "options": {}
      },
